{"updated_at": "2013-08-27T13:11:09Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2013-08-26T19:12:15Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/23287253", "id": 23287253, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/12015", "issue_id": 12015, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/garysweaver", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "8838005371ab9c0b1d40f0504bf8832a", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/8838005371ab9c0b1d40f0504bf8832a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F4eb6720c6cd70ee9e67ca6e4dc12e3df.png", "id": 92330, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/events{/privacy}", "login": "garysweaver", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garysweaver/followers"}, "body": "`where(...)` is not an equivalent to the old finders because it returns a relation, so there probably should be a statement below this section with something to the effect of, \"Note that `where(...)` returns a relation, not an array like the old finders. In some cases, the resulting relation can be treated similarly to an array, but if you require an array, use `where(...).to_a`.\"\r\n\r\nIf being really picky, you might also want to include a statement that the SQL executed may not be exactly the same, depending on how it is used.\r\n\r\nFeel free to disregard if you'd rather not make changes since it's committed.", "_id": {"$oid": "523be50ebd3543c151018ea7"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/12015#issuecomment-23287253"}
